editorialSummary.text: Consignment shop offering secondhand designer clothes, shoes & accessories for men & women.

originalText.text: Wow! Extraordinarily place, such great designs of the past! I went on a  psychedelic trip to the past! I bought a pair of orange red metic finish shoes from Nordstrom Rack for $60, and INA had a matching purse for $ 200.  My search continues, gladly knowing one exists.

originalText.text: I recently took several items to be consigned at this location. The people who answered my questions and priced my items were friendly and nice. When my items sold I got a check in the mail. I called a couple times to ask if anything else had sold and the people who answered my phone calls then were also very friendly and nice. I ended up selling two out of the five items. I recently picked up the remaining items that had not sold after calling them and letting them know I was coming ahead of time. I had brought a little duffel bag with me to bag up all the items. However, when I got there they had all of my stuff already in a shopping bag for me, and they even had wrapped the shoes in tissue paper, so it wouldn’t get the rest of my clothes dirty. So thoughtful! No issues with them and a good experience overall. Just wish some more of my stuff would have sold but that’s obviously not on them. Would consign here again. Also they have great stuff if youre looking to buy as well!

originalText.text: I own a consignment shop in Chicago and I when I travel to NYC I head straight to INA. I’ve been shopping here for years in all locations! The best selection the best prices that are totally reasonable. They are the nicest staff and so helpful and appreciative. Don’t even think of believing any bad reviews. Obviously someone was having a bad day. Thank you INA for all of your hard work to keep your stores going!

originalText.text:
Amazing place! found it by chance while walking to the gym, and immediately become my number one store in Manhattan. The lady and the gentleman who’s responsible on the store are very sweet and super nice. I was super amazed by their items, where I totally forgot myself trying every single piece, until I remembered that I’m supposed to be somewhere else for an appointment. I really wanted to buy that Dolce and Gabbana shoes, but I had to leave the store immediately. I asked them if they can leave it on the side for me, until I come back, and they didn’t hesitate a second to accommodate my request. Sure I came back late that evening and got that shoes and other things.
All the Love and Respect for this store and the people who’s taking charge of.

originalText.text:
I was there on a weekday afternoon and had fun checking on items that I figured I can use myself. I was a happy shopper there. Bought some really interesting 2nd hand stuff that I think were good deals. Almost empty of customers except myself plus the 2 workers and a consigner of branded goods for sale.

Back again today, still on pandemic & required to wear mask inside on a late afternoon on a cold winter weekday. They have great brands of high, well made quality items. Most seem to be used, a few are new, but they're all good. Got myself a pair of shoes and a backpack, I feel good getting them for myself. Good, friendly,  non intrusive service.
